CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 19, 1965, pg. 23, reads: "POWER TRIO - Three of the big reasons why the Pittsburgh Pirates are the talk of the baseball world these days can be found in performances of the three stars shown above. Left to right: Roberto Clemente, the 1964 batting champion; Willie Stargell and Donn Clendenon.  Clemente and Clendenon are hitting over .300, while Stargell is among the league's leaders in homers and RBIs. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Pirates baseball team players holding bats, including Roberto Clemente, #8 Willie Stargell, and #17 Donn Clendenon, with #10 Jim Pagliaroni in background, in dugout at Forbes Field
